HB 436 Engrossed 2026 Regular Session Dickerson
Abstract: Authorizes the secretary of the Dept. of Culture, Recreation and Tourism to
appoint veterans honorably discharged to serve as state park wardens.
Present law authorizes municipalities to exercise unlimited police power for the preservation
of peace and order in parks, playgrounds, swimming pools, and other amusement locations
operated by the municipality.
Present law allows police officers of the municipality to make arrests for violations of
ordinances within or without the corporate limits of the municipality.
Proposed law retains present law and authorizes the municipality or local governing
authority to appoint veterans to serve as police officers.
